{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "SCN015_WALL_PHONE_LIST",
      "sceneId": "SCN-015",
      "startNodeId": "INTRO_1",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "INTRO_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The wall phone list is laminated and warped, like it\u2019s been steamed by years of proximity to other people\u2019s problems. Most entries are crossed out in pen that\u2019s had time to become policy.",
          "next": "INTRO_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "INTRO_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A strip of newer tape sits over one column. The adhesive is still too clear to be old.",
          "next": "MENU_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_MAIN",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LOOK_LEGAL",
              "text": "look: Scan for Legal.",
              "next": "LOOK_LEGAL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_REST",
              "text": "look: Look over the rest of the list.",
              "next": "LOOK_REST_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_CALL",
              "text": "use: Use the wall phone to call the Legal extension.",
              "next": "CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_COMMIT",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_PRINT_ADDENDUM",
              "text": "ask: Ask the kiosk to print an approved contact addendum.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.factions",
                  "op": "in",
                  "value": [
                    "OLEA"
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "next": "PRINT_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away from the list.",
              "next": "END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_LEGAL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Legal.",
          "next": "LOOK_LEGAL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_LEGAL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You find it twice: once under \u201cCounsel,\u201d once under \u201cIncident Containment (Administrative).\u201d Same extension both times. Someone wanted it to survive edits.",
          "next": "LOOK_LEGAL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_LEGAL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The Legal line is printed in a newer font than the rest. It\u2019s the kind of update that says, quietly, \u201cWe will be consulted.\u201d",
          "next": "MENU_LEGAL"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_LEGAL",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_FROM_LEGAL",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_CALL_FROM_LEGAL",
              "text": "use: Call the Legal extension.",
              "next": "CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LOOK_REST_FROM_LEGAL",
              "text": "look: Look over the rest of the list.",
              "next": "LOOK_REST_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_REST_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Facilities routes to a number with an asterisk and no explanation. Safety has three different extensions, each labeled \u201cPRIMARY.\u201d",
          "next": "LOOK_REST_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "LOOK_REST_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Procurement is listed under a department name that reads like a confession. The only entry that looks maintained is Legal.",
          "next": "MENU_REST"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_REST",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_FROM_REST",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_2"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_CALL_FROM_REST",
              "text": "use: Call the Legal extension.",
              "next": "CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN_2",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The wall phone\u2019s handset is slightly tacky in the way only public plastic gets. The dial tone arrives immediately, as if it\u2019s been waiting to be useful.",
          "next": "CALL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The line connects with a click that sounds too modern for this building.",
          "next": "CALL_LEGAL_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_LEGAL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "LEGAL",
          "text": "Office of Legal Energy Assets, Counsel intake. This line is for procedural clarification only\u2014only\u2014and does not constitute authorization, approval, or a request for action.",
          "next": "CALL_LEGAL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_LEGAL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "LEGAL",
          "text": "If you are calling about \u201cclosure,\u201d please note: closure is a fiscal classification, not a physical condition. If you are calling about a physical condition, you are calling the wrong department, for everyone\u2019s benefit.",
          "next": "CALL_LEGAL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_LEGAL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "LEGAL",
          "text": "If you need someone to cite, cite \u201cCounsel Intake, extension listed.\u201d Do not cite a name. Names become invitations.",
          "next": "CALL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "CALL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The message ends cleanly. No option to leave a voicemail. The extension, at least, is real.",
          "next": "MENU_CALL"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_CALL",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_COPY_AFTER_CALL",
              "text": "use: Copy down the Legal extension.",
              "next": "COMMIT_COPY_AFTER_CALL_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN_3",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The lobby kiosk wakes with a fan noise that sounds irritated to be involved. Its screen offers a familiar OLEA header and an unfamiliar warning footer.",
          "next": "PRINT_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "KIOSK",
          "text": "CONTACT ADDENDUM (INTERNAL REFERENCE). This document is not a directory. This document is not a recommendation.",
          "next": "PRINT_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "KIOSK",
          "text": "Select contact to append to closure packet:",
          "next": "PRINT_4"
        },
        {
          "id": "PRINT_4",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Legal appears as the first suggestion, like it was already expecting to be attached.",
          "next": "MENU_PRINT"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_PRINT",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "USE_APPEND_PRINT_COMMIT",
              "text": "use: Append Legal extension and print.",
              "next": "COMMIT_PRINT_1"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_MAIN_4",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_COPY_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You write the extension exactly as shown, including the prefix nobody uses anymore. Your handwriting stays neat on purpose.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_COPY_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You add the extension to your working contacts as an escalation channel and supervisor reference. It feels like writing down a fire exit you hope you don\u2019t need.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_COPY_AFTER_CALL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You record the extension as a usable escalation channel, exactly as Legal suggested: impersonal, citable, and hard to argue with later. The paper trail gets heavier, which is the point.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "COMMIT_PRINT_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The kiosk prints a single strip of paper with the Legal extension and a timestamp. The font is official enough to be believed and cheap enough to be denied.",
          "next": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_NOTE_LEGAL_EXTENSION",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "note_legal_extension",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "paperwork.legalExtensionNoted",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.legalExtension",
              "action": "set",
              "value": "OLEA_LEGAL_EXTENSION"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LEAVE",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
